parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Threshold value for number of incoming X2 inter-frequency                                  handovers with cause "Handover Desirable for Radio Reasons" from                                    neighbor cells with coverage frequency. If incoming X2                                  inter-frequency handovers exceeds threshold, it is considered                                   related capacity cell is providing basic coverage support and                                   entering sleep state is prevented.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Time interval when sleep state is prohibited for capacity cell.                                    If set to 0, prohibition is disabled for related cell. When                                     related cell is in prohibition state, only value 0 can be                                   set.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Start time for sleep state prohibition. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. If empty, related                                     capacity cell is not prohibited from entering sleep state.                                  Otherwise, sleep state is prohibited until                                      capCellSleepProhibitInterval expires or                                     prohibition is disabled.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Indicates if hit rate table is cleaned up when related capacity                                    cell wakes up due to suspected coverage hole and automatic                                  coverage cell discovery is enabled.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Difference threshold for UE Lost rate between normal and sleep                                     statistics. If the threshold is exceeded, coverage cell wakes up                                    all capacity cells. Value 100 means monitoring for UE Lost is                                   disabled.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Difference threshold for RRC Connection Re-establishment rate                                  between normal and sleep statistics. If the threshold is                                    exceeded, coverage cell wakes up all capacity cells. Value 100                                  means monitoring for RRC Connection Re-establishment is                                     disabled.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Minimum required samples of UE Context Release to calculate UE                                     Lost rate for normal and sleep statistics.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Minimum required samples of RRC Connection Establishment Attempt                                   to calculate RRC Connection Re-establishment rate for normal and                                    sleep statistics.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Ratio indicating weight of latest data for normal statistics                                   calculation.

parameters.name: CellSleepFunction
parameters.description: Defines if MIMO sleep with "SWITCH" or "SOFT_SWITCH" mode is                                   allowed in the coverage cell. The "ADVANCED_SWITCH" mode is not                                     dependent on this attribute.

parameters.name: CellSleepNodeFunction
parameters.description: Minimum required hit rate value for related cell to be assigned                                    as coverage cell. When hit rate of the given cell is higher than                                    value, cell can be selected as coverage cell for capacity                                   cell.

parameters.name: ENodeBFunction
parameters.description: Minimum required hit rate to qualify a related cell as high hit                                     rate coverage cell by the Cell Sleep Mode feature.
